title: SonicWall: Connection Table Usage
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/network/sonicwall
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the connection table usage of SonicWall firewalls.
 It compares the current number of connections against the maximum and
 reports the usage in percent.

 The levels for the usage in percent can be configured via the rule
 "SonicWall Connections". Default levels are 80%/95%.

 The check uses the SONICWALL-FIREWALL-IP-STATISTICS-MIB.

item:
 The index of the connection table entry.

discovery:
 One service is created for each connection table entry.
